<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-523-281  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 523 281.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Oct 11 1990 n1235 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Automate and informate. (BCS News)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zuboff, Shoshana.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Shoshana Zuboff delivered the annual Unisys lecture to the BritishComputer Society (BCS) at the Royal Society in London.andP;  Thebiggest obstacles to exploiting the strategic potential inherentin information technology are not the technology itself, but theforms of organization and conceptions of management that continueto dominate.andP;  The goals associated with deploying the newtechnology are typically related to cost reduction, efficiency,productivity, and reducing the number of employees.andP;  Informationtechnology offers more than mere automation, it also turnsautomated activities into data and displays the data.andP;  It rendersprocesses, objects, behavior and events in a visible, knowable andshareable new way.andP;  The application of information technologyrequires the construction of a new type of knowledge that is moreanalytical, abstract and conceptual.andP;  Tips for constructing suchan organization are provided.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AutomationInformation TheoryBritish Computer Society.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>